{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-4329"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Other Construction Installation"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "4329"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :construction/other-installation
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :hazmat-containment :trade-craft-quality]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :installation-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics false
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:identity :forms :audit-ledger :notifications]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "`:installation-governor` is implemented end-to-end in `src/installation`
 as an OTHER-CONSTRUCTION-INSTALLATION-PROJECT OPERATIONS COORDINATION
 actor -- Installation Advisor (LLM proposal-only) ⊣ Installation Governor
 (closed-op-allowlist / site-verification / pre-work hazmat-survey /
 fall-protection / unresolved-concern hard-gates). Deliberately narrower
 in authority than the `cloud-itonami-isic-4211` (construction) robotics-
 premise reference this actor follows structurally, and structured after
 the sibling `cloud-itonami-isic-4330` (building completion and
 finishing) coordination-only actor: `:itonami.blueprint/robotics` is
 honestly `false` here -- this actor holds NO trade-equipment-control
 authority and NO installation-completion-sign-off authority (both are
 HARD, permanent governor blocks, never overridable by human approval --
 see `installation.governor` ns docstring). Every one of its four
 proposal ops (`:log-site-record` / `:schedule-installation-operation` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:order-supplies`) carries `:effect :propose`
 ONLY -- the governor HARD-holds any proposal that doesn't
 (`effect-not-propose-violations`), a structural invariant distinguishing
 this actor from siblings that DO commit real-world actuation effects.
 Covers building-installation trade work outside 4321 (electrical) / 4322
 (plumbing, heat and air-conditioning installation): thermal/acoustic
 insulation, sound-proofing, elevator/escalator installation, and other
 specialty building installation work not elsewhere classified.
 Per-jurisdiction pre-work hazmat-survey / fall-protection legal-basis
 catalog (JPN/USA/DEU, `installation.facts`) with real official sources
 (independently verified against laws.e-gov.go.jp / osha.gov /
 eur-lex.europa.eu / baua.de before being written), and mail+phone
 safety-concern notification (`installation.notify`, a portable `.cljc`
 caller-injected transport seam -- no JVM interop, per this repo's
 cljs-first mandate) to the site's supervisor/safety-officer contact
 roster. `:flag-safety-concern` ALWAYS escalates to a human, at every
 phase, unconditionally. Like `cloud-itonami-isic-4330` and UNLIKE
 `cloud-itonami-isic-4311`/`cloud-itonami-isic-4210`,
 `:schedule-installation-operation` here is NOT a permanent `high-stakes`
 member -- it MAY auto-commit at phase 3 once every HARD check clears and
 confidence is high, reflecting building-installation trade work's
 materially lower risk profile relative to demolition or heavy-civil
 earthwork scheduling (see `installation.governor`/`installation.phase`
 ns docstrings for the full rationale). See `docs/` -- README `Actuation`
 section -- for the full governor-check enumeration and the rationale for
 each hard/soft rule."}
